overall_summary: The discord community is heavily focused on the controversial GOLD token launch and insider trading allegations, while technical development shifts toward the elizaOS V2.0.0 dynamic execution engine and new plugin integrations.
key_facts: Shaw acknowledged critical liquidity pool management errors in the GOLD 'gold presale' token launch that damaged the token supply.
The Sportradar ElizaOS Plugin v.01 was released on GitHub, providing live NBA data access for prediction agents.
Discord plugin version 1.3.8 was released to resolve audit log permission errors and private field access failures.
Hyperfy announced the permanent shutdown of its legacy platform at hyperfy.io on April 1st, 2026, transitioning to a self-hosted model.
PR #6384 introduced a new validation-aware, schema-driven prompt execution path for the V2.0.0 dynamic execution engine.
CJFT launched an official token and demonstrated utility through live-streamed hardware integrations.
A proposal was submitted to send airdrop tokens to an immutable smart contract that buys/burns ElizaOS based on price oracles to optimize tax implications.
Users reported persistent login failures on ElizaCloud due to server-side exceptions, requiring hard refreshes for temporary resolution.
open_questions: Is elizacloud currently using OpenAI GPT-4?
What is the cap for the upcoming airdrops mentioned in the partners channel?

new_issues_prs.title: V2.0.0: dynamic execution engine
new_issues_prs.author: odilitime
new_issues_prs.significance: Introduces schema-driven prompt execution paths and retry logic with backoff for the next generation of the framework.

new_issues_prs.title: feat(v2.0.0): wasm agent runtime
new_issues_prs.author: revlentless
new_issues_prs.significance: Enables the Rust core to run in browser/Node.js environments via WebAssembly.

new_issues_prs.title: Eligibility Mismatch & Snapshot Bug - Tangem Hardware Wallet
new_issues_prs.author: Zenobow
new_issues_prs.significance: Reported discrepancies in token migration eligibility for hardware wallet users.

overall_focus.claim: Development is split between hardening V1 infrastructure (v1.7.2) and architectural foundation work for V2.0.0, including a Python-based bridge and Rust WASM compatibility.

discord_updates.summary: Focused on GOLD token controversy, specifically allegations of insider trading and a 40% dev wallet. Community expressed frustration over project prioritization and monetization transparency.
Resolution of Discord plugin v1.3.8 issues and the release of the Sportradar integration. Discussion on building prediction agents similar to Polymarket using multi-AI competition models.
Strategic discussions regarding tax-efficient airdrop mechanisms using buy-and-burn smart contracts and the sunset timeline for Hyperfy legacy hosting.

user_feedback.feedback_summary: Users expressed significant concern regarding the proliferation of new tokens instead of focusing on the Eliza Cloud monetization and value for original Eliza OS holders.
Positive feedback received regarding the Migration Agent's use of Claude Sonnet for its human-like interaction and structured responses.

strategic_insights.insight: The recurring pattern of unannounced or poorly executed side-token launches is creating a trust gap that threatens to overshadow core technical progress on ElizaOS.
implications_or_questions: How can the team standardize tokenomics for sub-projects to prevent community backlash?
Does the focus on multiple tokens distract from the Eliza Cloud resource-intensive priority?

market_analysis.observation: Hyperfy is pivoting from an NFT-based platform model to an open-source, self-hosted service model with the sunset of hyperfy.io.
market_analysis.relevance: Reflects a broader industry trend of moving away from NFT gating toward open infrastructure and token-based platform ownership.
